    "Extended limit = ±∞ when both sides agree; opposite infinities mean DNE.",
    "Degree rule and divide-by-highest-power for limits at infinity.",
    "Horizontal asymptote = limit at ±∞; vertical asymptote = one-sided infinite limits at finite a."
